race.comment: UNLIMITED (2) is back in Sydney after a successful sojourn south. Scored two back over this distance at Caulfield then charged home to finish second to the highly regarded Gilded Water over 2000m at the same track last time. Given a 39-day let-up which is the query but McDonald's booking allays those fears. BRIGIDINE GAL (7) dropped back in grade last time but was a shade disappointing over the mile at Warwick Farm after getting a long way back. Placed in the Gr 3 Epona over 1900m last prep so a bit more ground today will suit. KIND WORDS (6) ran on well without threatening first-up behind subsequent winner Dance To The Boom at the Kenso. No placings from five second-up runs dampens the enthusiasm a little. POCKETING (1) ran a better race over 2000m here last start and is rock hard fit now after four runs back. INQUIRING MINDS (5) has been plain in his two runs this prep but should improve out to this distance.
